    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-01T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-01T02:00:00-05:00" n="99"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d99">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.24/951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Asmara</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asmara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-01T10:00:00+03:00"
                            >February 1, 1943—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:57 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. General Maxwell<note n="6" xml:id="d99fn6">Maj. Gen. R. L. Maxwell,
                        Commanding General, Services of Supply, U. S. Army Forces in the Middle
                        East</note> and Colonel Clark Commanding Officer Asmara will be at Addis
                    Ababa February 9. Colonel Clark suggests <pb facs="0096" n="84" xml:id="pg_84"/>
                    I go up with him to report to the Department probable inquiries on lease-lend by
                    Emperor. Shall I proceed?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
